HEADWORD: Isochronal
<hw>I*soch"ro*nal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Isochronous</er>.]</ety> <def>Uniform in time; of equal time;
performed in equal times; recurring at regular intervals; <as>as,
<ex>isochronal</ex> vibrations or oscillations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isochronic</ent>⟦br⟧
